HEADWORD: Underglaze
<hw>Un"der*glaze`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Applied under
the glaze, that is, before the glaze is put on; fitted to be so applied;
-- said of colors in porcelain painting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undergo</ent>⟦br⟧
